      • addOrUpdateAlbumContest

        public void addOrUpdateAlbumContest(Map<String,Object> params,
                           ISirqulCallback<AlbumContestResponse> callback)
        Creates or updates an album contest.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/contest

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account ID of the user
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          the application key. Maps to "gameType".
        • SirqulKeys.contestType
          a custom field used for aggregation and searching
        • SirqulKeys.albumContestId
          the album contest ID for updating (don't pass in if creating)
        • SirqulKeys.title
          the title of the contest
        • SirqulKeys.description
          the description of the contest
        • SirqulKeys.albumId1
          the album ID for the first album
        • SirqulKeys.removeAlbum1
          removes album1 from the contest
        • SirqulKeys.albumId2
          the album ID for the second album
        • SirqulKeys.removeAlbum2
          removes album2 from the contest
        • SirqulKeys.startDate
          the start date of the contest (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        • SirqulKeys.endDate
          the end date of the contest (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        • SirqulKeys.publicRead
          determines whether the contest's participants has read permissions
        • SirqulKeys.publicWrite
          determines whether the contest's participants has write permissions
        • SirqulKeys.publicDelete
          determines whether the contest's participants has delete permissions
        • SirqulKeys.publicAdd
          determines whether the contest's participants has add permissions
        • SirqulKeys.locationDescription
          the location description of the contest taking place
        • SirqulKeys.visibility
          the determines the album's participants ( Enums.Visibility .PUBLIC - includes everyone in the system as a potential participant, Enums.Visibility.PRIVATE - only considers people who have been invited as participants)
        • SirqulKeys.connectionIdsToAdd
          list of connection IDs
        • SirqulKeys.connectionGroupIdsToAdd
          list of connection group IDs
        • SirqulKeys.includeFriendGroup
          determines whether to include all friends as participants
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          location used to update the user's current location

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        AlbumContestResponse on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:

      • approveAlbumContest

        public void approveAlbumContest(Map<String,Object> params,
                       ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Sets the approval status of an album contest. Only an approval status of APPROVED or FEATURED will be returned when searching for public content. Only someone with EXECUTIVE rights or rights to edit the application can approve/feature the content.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/contest/approve

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, device id sent automatically)
        • SirqulKeys.albumContestId
          The ID of the album contest
        • SirqulKeys.approvalStatus
          The approval status to set {PENDING, REJECTED, APPROVED, FEATURED}

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call.
